article.headline: Valparaiso 72, Liberty 54
article.story: TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) -- Dan Oppland had 13 points and 11 rebounds, leading Valparaiso to a 72-54 win over Liberty in the consolation game of the Fiesta Bowl Classic on Tuesday night. No. 4 Arizona went after its 18th title in the tournament's 19 years in the next game, playing Louisiana-Lafayette. Ali Berdiel led the Crusaders (3-6) with 17 points, and Ron Howard scored 14. Liberty's Larry Blair had 20 points, but couldn't prevent the Flames (3-9) from losing their fourth straight. Oppland scored the first nine points in a 15-4 run that carried the Crusaders to a 52-41 lead with 12:33 remaining in the second half. Jimmie Miles extended the lead to 58-43 with two free throws at the 9:04 mark. In the next two minutes, Liberty's Ryan Mantlo made two layups but missed the front end of a one-and-one, and Oppland's two free throws with 6:51 to go got Valparaiso's lead back to 60-47. Berdiel, who had 12 points in the first half, punctuated the win when he stole a pass, beat a defender with a behind-the-back move and scored with 1:37 to go, increasing the lead to 67-52. The Flames led by as many as eight points in the first half before Valparaiso came back. The Crusaders went ahead 34-33 on two free throws by Berdiel with 3:17 to go,and 36-33 on Oumar Sylla's baseline jumper with 2:25 left. But Blair made a 3-pointer with 1:48 to play, and the teams were tied at 37 at halftime.
